This repository contains a C++ implementation of the Google logging
module.  Documentation for the implementation is in doc/.

See INSTALL for (generic) installation instructions for C++: basically
   ./autogen.sh && ./configure && make && make install

Or, with Bazel, add the following snippet to the WORKSPACE file:

    git_repository(
        name = "com_github_google_glog",
        remote = "https://github.com/google/glog.git",
        commit = 'ad2743c33ac9ac51ab6c9c7fe8bc619c4a1a3ad6',
    )
    # By default, glog depends on gflags.
    git_repository(
        name = "com_github_gflags_gflags",
        remote = "https://github.com/gflags/gflags.git",
        tag = 'v2.2.1',
    )

Then you can reference the glog library in BUILD files like this:

    @com_github_google_glog//:glog
